cpu-ec-reporter for Debian
==================

cpu-ec-reporter is a lightweight utility set that:
- Periodically reads CPU temperature and reports it to the EC via serial
- Reports suspend/resume status changes to the EC through a systemd-sleep hook
- Initializes RTL8211F NIC LED trigger behavior

Installed units and scripts
---------------------------

- core_temp_rpt.service: one-shot service that sends temperature data to the EC.
- core_temp_rpt.timer: triggers core_temp_rpt.service periodically.
- serial_buad_set.service: sets ttyS1 baud rate before the timer starts.
- stmmac_led.service: applies RTL8211F LED trigger settings.
- /usr/lib/systemd/system-sleep/pm2ec: reports pre/post suspend state to the EC.

